tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jfl1692010192230.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jfl1692010192230.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jfl1692010192230.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"avi1665702784986\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Uniface Application Architecture\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"avi1665702784986__uniface_application_architecture_14162\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface applications are based on a client/server architecture in which the user interface runs on the client and all other functionality runs on a server.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"avi1665702784986__p_d2681e1_d2682e1_d2683e1\">The runtime engine executes the application components when it receives instructions to do so, either from the user or from other components. It ensures that presentation components are displayed to the user and sends and receives data via a DBMS driver.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"avi1665702784986__p_d2684e1_d2685e1_d2686e1\">At its simplest, a Uniface application can run in standalone mode on a single machine that fills both client and server roles.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"avi1665702784986__fig_d2687e1_d2688e1_d2689e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Standalone Client/Server Application</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Architecture of a standalone Uniface application\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/unifaceappstandalone.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"avi1665702784986__li_d953e1_d954e1_d955e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">The Uniface runtime engine executes the application components. It ensures that\n                  presentation components are displayed to the user and sends and receives data via\n                  a DBMS driver.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"avi1665702784986__li_d956e1_d957e1_d958e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Uniface connectors (also known as drivers) enable Uniface to display a user\n                  interface, communicate over a network, access databases, and integrate with other\n                  technologies. These connectors give Uniface great flexibility in running on\n                  different platforms and in different environments. They also make it possible to\n                  use Uniface as an application integrator.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"avi1665702784986__p_d2693e1_d2694e1_d2695e1\">The basic architecture can be varied in many ways because Uniface supports web, mobile, and desktop applications that can be deployed in a distributed environment, in which web servers, databases, and Uniface application servers may be located on different networked servers.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"avi1665702784986__p_d2696e1_d2697e1_d2698e1\">The degree to which Uniface applications can be partitioned is dependent on the application design. For example, it is possible distribute an application so that forms run on the client and services run on a central server. For a web application, server pages are executed by a web application server that can communicate with services running in a Uniface application server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"avi1665702784986__p_d2699e1_d2700e1_d2701e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xxw1665702741737.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xxw1665702741737.html\" title=\"In a desktop or client/server Uniface application, Form components run on the client to provide the user interface, and Service components run on remote servers to access databases and provide centralized processing.\">Distributed Client/Server Applications</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zwb1665702684890.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zwb1665702684890.html\" title=\"Uniface web applications run in a Uniface Web Application Server and are invoked by the client browser over the internet.\">Uniface Web Applications</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"avi1665702784986__p_d2702e1_d2703e1_d2704e1\">The Uniface connectors include:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"avi1665702784986__li_d959e1_d960e1_d961e1\">A user interface connector that provides a graphical user interface (GUI) or character-based user interface (CHUI) for the application.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"avi1665702784986__li_d962e1_d963e1_d964e1\">A network connector to access remote resources via TCP/IP. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"avi1665702784986__li_d965e1_d966e1_d967e1\">One or more DBMS connectors to access databases.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"avi1665702784986__li_d968e1_d969e1_d970e1\">Other connectors for accessing other technologies, such as\n            COM, SOAP, and LDAP directories. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4573792\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4573792\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Application Architecture Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Application Architecture Uniface applications are based on a client/server architecture in which the user interface runs on the client and all other functionality runs on a server. The runtime engine executes the application components when it receives instructions to do so, either from the user or from other components. It ensures that presentation components are displayed to the user and sends and receives data via a DBMS driver. At its simplest, a Uniface application can run in standalone mode on a single machine that fills both client and server roles. Figure 1. Standalone Client/Server Application The Uniface runtime engine executes the application components. It ensures that presentation components are displayed to the user and sends and receives data via a DBMS driver. Uniface connectors (also known as drivers) enable Uniface to display a user interface, communicate over a network, access databases, and integrate with other technologies. These connectors give Uniface great flexibility in running on different platforms and in different environments. They also make it possible to use Uniface as an application integrator. The basic architecture can be varied in many ways because Uniface supports web, mobile, and desktop applications that can be deployed in a distributed environment, in which web servers, databases, and Uniface application servers may be located on different networked servers. The degree to which Uniface applications can be partitioned is dependent on the application design. For example, it is possible distribute an application so that forms run on the client and services run on a central server. For a web application, server pages are executed by a web application server that can communicate with services running in a Uniface application server. For more information, see Distributed Client/Server Applications and Uniface Web Applications . The Uniface connectors include: A user interface connector that provides a graphical user interface (GUI) or character-based user interface (CHUI) for the application. A network connector to access remote resources via TCP/IP. One or more DBMS connectors to access databases. Other connectors for accessing other technologies, such as COM, SOAP, and LDAP directories. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}